// FYI: MANY of the 'corrupted' errors come from failed thread interrupting. new GMI arrived, waits for interruption, and the worker threads happily continue
// when the worker threads note the new block (sometimes even 10-30s later!) in the meantime another GMI could show up and invalidate the previous already..
// happens on BOOM often
// also might happen in conjunction with coin switch: mining boom at 100, switch to BHD, in the mean time GMI Boom comes with 101, BHD ends, Boom continues with 100
// also some submissions are reported as wrong due to network lag and GMI:
// Boom mining at 100, found DL, queued for submitting, new GMI arrived, Boom now at 101, confirmer picks up old DL from 100 and tries to send it -> failure
// Same happens when the confirmer managed to SEND before GMI arrived, but is waiting for confirmation and GMI arrives in the meanwhile - error is reported, even though it's irrelevant error
